│ pass remaps uses of values from the first loop to the second loop after merging them.                                                                                                    │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ Specifically, when the exit block of the first loop is merged into the second loop, the LCSSA PHI node within it (`%sum1.0.lcssa`) becomes a regular PHI node. Its predecessors change.  │
│ The `loop-fusion` pass must correctly update the incoming blocks for this PHI node. The crash suggests this is not happening correctly.                                                  │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ Looking at the IR, `%sum1.0.lcssa` is in `for.end`, which has one predecessor, `for.inc`. After fusion, `for.end` is merged into the second loop. The block that was `for.end` will now  │
│ have a new predecessor, which is the new latch of the fused loop (derived from `for.inc6`). The original predecessor `for.inc` is now part of the fused loop body and no longer a direct │
│ predecessor.                                                                                                                                                                             │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The `loop-fusion` pass uses `remapInstructionsInLoop` to update instructions. It seems this function, or the logic calling it, doesn't correctly handle the transformation of an LCSSA   │
│ PHI into a regular PHI in this context.                                                                                                                                                  │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ A common pattern for fixing such bugs is to ensure that when instructions are moved or blocks are rewired, all PHI nodes are correctly updated. In this case, after merging the first    │
│ loop's exit block into the second loop, the PHI node `%sum1.0.lcssa` needs to be updated. Its single incoming edge from `for.inc` needs to be replaced. The new value should come from   │
│ the corresponding iteration of the fused loop.                                                                                                                                           │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The value `%add` is defined inside the first loop. After fusion, its uses outside the first loop's original body need to be remapped. The use in `%sum1.0.lcssa` is one such case. The   │
│ remapping should probably use a value defined within the fused loop's body.                                                                                                              │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The problem is that `for.end` becomes part of the fused loop. The PHI `%sum1.0.lcssa` is now inside the fused loop. Its predecessor `for.inc` is also inside the fused loop. This is not │
